snippet.description:
And now… a leap into the unknown. New trailer for #28YearsLater: The Bone Temple. Only in cinemas January 14.

Expanding upon the world created by Danny Boyle and Alex Garland in 28 Years Later - but turning that world on its head - Nia DaCosta directs 28 Years Later: The Bone Temple. In a continuation of the epic story, Dr. Kelson (Ralph Fiennes) finds himself in a shocking new relationship - with consequences that could change the world as they know it - and Spike's (Alfie Williams) encounter with Jimmy Crystal (Jack O'Connell) becomes a nightmare he can't escape. In the world of The Bone Temple, the infected are no longer the greatest threat to survival - the inhumanity of the survivors can be stranger and more terrifying.

snippet.title: The Magic Faraway Tree | Official Teaser Trailer
snippet.description:
The Magic Faraway Tree follows Polly (Claire Foy), Tim (Andrew Garfield) and their three children - a modern family forced to relocate to the remote English countryside. As they adapt to their new lives, the children discover a magical tree and its extraordinary and eccentric residents including treasured characters Moonface (Nonso Anozie), Silky (Nicola Coughlan), Dame Washalot (Jessica Gunning) and Saucepan Man (Dustin Demri-Burns). At the top of the tree, they are transported to spectacular and fantastical lands and, through the joys and challenges of their adventures, the family learn to reconnect and value each other for the first time in years.

THE MAGIC FARAWAY TREE is released by Entertainment Film Distributors in UK and Ireland cinemas on 27 March 2026

snippet.description:
#Netflix #StrangerThings #StrangerThings5

🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
Stranger Things returns for its most intense chapter yet in this fan-made concept trailer for Stranger Things Season 5. Featuring characters like Eleven, Will Byers, Mike Wheeler, Dustin, Lucas, Max, Jonathan Byers, Joyce Byers, Steve Harrington, and Chief Hopper, this trailer imagines the final battle against Vecna. Inspired by Netflix’s official tone and the epic energy of the Stranger Things 5 Final Season Trailer 2, this edit aims to capture the drama, tension, and emotional stakes of the show’s last season.

The inspiration behind this video:
Prepare for the beginning of the end with the Stranger Things Season 5 Trailer, the highly anticipated look at the Stranger Things 5 Final Season trailer 2. As Netflix gears up for the massive conclusion of its flagship series, we break down every secret hidden in the Stranger Things 5 Official Teaser. Whether you are searching for the stranger things season 5 volume 2 trailer, the stranger things 5 trailer, or updates on stranger things season 5 part 2, this video covers it all. The st5 trailer teases an apocalyptic showdown, and our analysis of the stranger things final trailer explores how the saga will close.

The stakes have never been higher as Vecna (played by Jamie Campbell Bower) threatens to destroy the world, forcing Eleven (Millie Bobby Brown) to make the ultimate sacrifice. In this breakdown of the stranger things 5 volume 2 trailer, we explore the fates of Max (Sadie Sink), Lucas (Caleb McLaughlin), Dustin (Gaten Matarazzo), and Will Byers (Noah Schnapp). We also dive into the arcs for Chief Hopper (David Harbour), Joyce Byers (Winona Ryder), Mike Wheeler (Finn Wolfhard), and the older teens including Steve Harrington (Joe Keery), Maya Hawke, Natalia Dyer, Charlie Heaton, and Cara Buono. Every frame of the stranger things season 5 part 2 trailer hints at who lives and who dies.

snippet.title: The God Slayer - Official Gameplay Reveal Trailer
snippet.description:
Enjoy this nine-minute gameplay reveal trailer for The God Slayer, the upcoming open-world steampunk fantasy RPG from Pathea Games, creators of the My Time series. It's in development for PC, PS5, and Xbox Series X|S. 

The developers describe The God Slayer as follows: "Enter an Eastern-inspired steampunk metropolis where gods known as Celestials reign with a divine fist! In this premium open-world RPG, you are an Elemancer who refuses to bow to his creators. Infused with elemental powers and a heart of vengeance, you will dethrone them all. You will rise to be The God Slayer."

Wishlist The God Slayer on Steam if you're interested: https://store.steampowered.com/app/2536510/

snippet.description:
Audrey Hobert’s new album, ‘Who’s the Clown?’ is available now. Listen here: https://audreyhobert.lnk.to/whostheclown
Order 'Who's the Clown?' magazine & CD here: https://audreyhobert.lnk.to/shop 
 
Follow Audrey:
https://www.instagram.com/audreyhobert/?hl=en
https://www.tiktok.com/@_mikemonster?lang=en
https://x.com/audreyhobert1
https://www.audreyhobert.net/

Credits:
Director: Audrey Hobert
EP / Producer: Will Noyce
Producer: Arpi Hamzoian
HOP: Vladen Ponomar

SVP of RCA Creative: Niki Roberton
RCA Creative Manager: Shoshana Reist 
Artist Manager: Sophie Lev 

DP: Adrian Nieto
1st AC: Billy Briggs
                     
Gaffer: Evan Crocker
Swing: Jaron Fonseca
       
Key Grip: Mason Mclaury
                     
Production Designer: Wesley Goodrich
Set Dresser: Cleo Camp
Set Dresser: Delon Isaacs
              
HMU: Ciara Maccaro
Edited by Audrey Hobert & Will Noyce 
Color: Brian Charles 

Lyrics:
This isn’t Sex and the City
Nobody’s watching me write in my room
And anyway, when I get home, I take off my cool clothes
‘Cause why would I stay in those?
I go to the bar
That’s monumental
And if he’s hot and seems into it, it’s accidental
What’s it like to be admired
Hot and desired
This isn’t Sex and the City
Nobody sees me and knows of my column
Nobody sees me at all is the problem
But of course when they do, they’re not the one that I want to
But I go to the bar
I’m a believer
So if it’s not in the stars, then I don’t want it either
I say goodbye and take the bottle
I’ve never been stronger
Call the Uber and I tell ‘em turn it up
Tell ‘em turn it up, baby
That’s my song they’re playing
Baby turn it up, could you turn it up maybe?
‘Cause I’m drunk and I’m high
So I’m crossed
Didn’t score any guys so I’m lost
That’s all for now, Mr. Driver
I’m rating you five stars
If this was Sex and the City
I’d get in and he would’ve already called me
But instead I’m in the shower
Gotta feel a warm touch somehow
Now I’m ready to go back out
And he’s here at the bar
God, is he boring
I wanna wake up in make-up with him in the morning
He calls a car to his apartment
I guess there’s a God, then
The seat is up
The place is haunted
He’s heating up and eating up a pizza pocket
I wanted one, but he forgot it
He’s off his meds
And he’s an artist
Touching my leg
You don’t have a headboard
Do that again
I think that I want more
If this is it, then what is it all for?
Let’s make it quick
Then I’m leaving out the front door
Call the uber and I tell ‘em turn it up
Tell ‘em turn it up, baby
That shit’s overrated
Baby turn it up, could you turn it up maybe?
I was drunk, I was high, I was crossed
He’s the love of my life, no he’s not
I could’ve guessed
I’m swearing by it
But I guess you never know until you go and try it
What it’s like to be admired
Hot and desired

#AudreyHobert #Sexandthecity #WhostheClown?

snippet.title: Flea - A Plea (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Flea's "A Plea" is out now on Nonesuch Records: https://flea.lnk.to/APlea 

Flea — Electric Bass, Vocals and Trumpet 

Anna Butterss — Upright Bass, Vocals 
Deantoni Parks — Drums, Vocals 
Jeff Parker — Guitar, Vocals 
Mauro Refosco — Percussion 
Rickey Washington — Alto Flute 
Vikram Devasthali — Trombone 
Chris Warren — Vocals 
Josh Johnson — Alto Saxophone, Vocals 

Directed By: Clara Balzary 
Produced By: Corrine Dye 
Production Company: First Matter 
Cinematography By: Jimmy Nyeango 
Choreography By: Sadie Wilking 
Edited By: Sid Williams 

1st AD: Lewis Rangal 
1st AC: Govinda Angulo 
Camera A - Gimbal Operator: Jason Robbins 
Camera B Operator: Justice Vaughn Ott 
Gaffer: Kevin Kim Best 
Electric: Paul Kane 
Electrics: Noah Shettel, Vahagan Gukasyan, Michael Roseman 
Key Grip: Greg Karamov 
Best Grip: Tyler Johnson-Williams

DIT: Raffaele Vesco 
VTR Operator: Ben Cohen

Makeup Artist: Katie Mann 
Colorist: Connor Bailey 
Finishing: Mahyar Mandegar 
Production Assistants: Richard Monteiro, Jadyn Norris Sarno, Sophie Savides

Set Medic: Gabriel Frolick 
Catering: Beezoo 
Casting: SJ Hasman 
Artist Management: Guy Oseary, Elana Radin 
Video Commissioner: Devin Sarno 
Special Thanks: Cabin Edit, G&J Grip, House Post, Old Fast Glass, Silverlake Conservatory of Music, Walk & Talk 


A PLEA 

(Civil War) 
I hear it in the air  
I feel it in the air  
Who’s your neighbor, who’s your friend?  
Ahh there’s hate all around 

I dont care about your fucking politics  
I don’t wanna hear about your politics  
Well, he said boo  
She said hooray 

Now we are human beings right here  
Human beings We’re here together  

Come on 

Whatcha gonna do? Whatcha gonna do when it falls on you? 

You’re scaring the kids  
The beautiful kids  
Ah yeah they wanna know  
The children wanna know  
Is the ugly coming, and the guns?  
Is the army coming, blotting out the sun?  
The blood red sun, the blood red sun  
Ahhhhhhh concentration camps? 

(Peace and Love) 

My blood runs cold  
I’m feeling hate all around  
It’s no solution  
It’s never been a solution 

Come on Are you with me? 
We all know what it is 

Build a bridge Shine a light 

Make something beautiful  
I don’t care if it’s a little scrap of squiggly crayon on a paper  
Make something beautiful and see somebody  
Give it to somebody  

I’m not being corny this shit is real 

Live for peace Live for love 

It’s all we got 

See the god in everyone  
See the god 

Come on with me 

(The Æther) 

Everyone just wants to be loved  
See the god in everyone  
Everyone leaves out no-one  
And everything besides love is cowardice  
You wanna be brave, you wanna be tough?  
Peace and love is the toughest hardest thing you can do 

Build a bridge that's where the courage is 

Shine your light Shine it true 

Yeah

And everything besides love is cowardice  
You wanna be brave, you wanna be tough?  
Peace and love is the toughest hardest thing you can do 

Build a bridge that's where the courage is 

Shine your light Shine it true 

Yeah

snippet.title: Season 20: Vendetta Official Trailer | Overwatch 2
snippet.description:
A new villain steps into the spotlight with the arrival of our first official melee Damage Hero, Vendetta. With unmatched mobility, devastating close-range power, and a hunger for domination, Vendetta fights to reclaim her father’s legacy with deep ties to Talon and the next chapter of Overwatch 2’s global story.

Stadium levels up once again with Doomfist and Wuyang stepping into the arena, and the arrival of a brand new China Control map. We’re also giving players a rank reset and new rewards to chase as they keep climbing up the leaderboards.

Deck the halls as you brawl with the wintery cosmetics in the Season 20 Battle Pass. And with the 80 Mythic Prisms you’ll earn, bring some western flair to your festivities with the new Divine Desperado Cassidy Mythic Skin.

Winter Wonderland is back with a magical twist on a fan-favorite mode! Enjoy Mischief & Magic on a festive-themed map and with fun holiday props. And on week three of the event, get ready for “When Props Attack,” where props gain the ability to finally fight back.

And that’s just the beginning! Enjoy new Battle Pass and Shop skins, returning favorites, new surprises, and so much more.

Vengeance arrives when Season 20: Vendetta starts on Dec 9!

Overwatch 2 is free to play for everyone on console & PC!

_
